# Cursor AI Rules for Restaurant Menu SaaS

## Core Stack
- Framework: Next.js (App Router)
- Language: TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Animations: Framer Motion
- State Management: Zustand
- Backend/DB: Supabase

## Development Rules
1. ALWAYS use Next.js App Router conventions (layout.tsx, page.tsx).
2. Write clean, modular, and reusable React functional components.
3. Use Tailwind CSS for ALL styling. DO NOT use raw CSS or inline styles unless strictly necessary for dynamic theme variables.
4. Support Multi-tenancy: Rely on CSS Variables (e.g., `var(--primary)`) in Tailwind config to allow dynamic theming per restaurant.
5. Mobile-First Approach: Build components for mobile screens first, then scale up using `md:` and `lg:` prefixes.
6. RTL & Bilingual Support: Use logical Tailwind properties (e.g., `ms-4`, `pe-2`) instead of physical ones (`ml-4`, `pr-2`) to seamlessly support Arabic (RTL) and English (LTR).
7. Animations: Keep them subtle and elegant using Framer Motion (e.g., smooth fade-ins, gentle scale on tap). Avoid heavy animations.
8. NEVER generate dummy data if database schema is provided; refer to `@docs/Database-Schema.md`.
9. Always read `@docs/PRD.md` and `@docs/Design-System.md` before creating new complex UI features.